    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TELECOM OWNERSHIP SHUFFLE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Spain's Telefonica SA will receive $800 million from Brasil Telecom for Telefonica's 31 percent stake in CRT, a southern Brazilian phone company (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Spanish telecommunications company Telefonica will receive $800 million from Brasil Telecom for Telefonica's 31 percent stake in the southern Brazilian phone company CRT. Telefonica was forced to sell its stake after Brazil's telecommunications regulator, Anatel, ruled that the Spanish company could not own a majority stake in two of Brazil's fixed-line companies. Telefonica bought Sao Paulo fixed-line operator Telesp in 1998.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
